   Garden Party 2012
   Virginia Museum of Fine Arts

   2nd Annual Logo







   The American Diabetes Association’s 2nd Annual Garden Party will bring
   the community together for a fabulous night of fun, supporting our
   mission to find the cure for diabetes and to improve the lives of all
   people with this disease. This spectacular event will take place in the
   beautiful surroundings of the Pauley Center at the Virginia Museum of
   Fine Arts. The evening will feature gourmet hors d'oeuvres, open bars,
   live and silent auctions, entertainment by the Kings of Swing, and a
   one-of-a-kind wine giveaway.

   The Garden Party will raise much needed funds for diabetes research,
   education and advocacy efforts. Join area individuals, businesses,
   organizations and community leaders in support of the 131,000 Greater
   Richmond area residents with diabetes. We will celebrate diabetes care
   and the commitment to one day finding the cure for this devastating
   disease.

   **Please note: Seating for this event is limited. Reserve your table or
   tickets now.**

     Couple Table Decor 2 Kings of Swing Woman with Hat

    REMEMBER:
   *        The mission of the American Diabetes Association is to prevent
   and cure diabetes and to improve the lives of all people affected by
   diabetes.
   *        1 in 3 Americans will have diabetes by the year 2050, if
   current trends continue
   *        Diabetes kills more Americans than breast cancer and AIDS
   combined
   *        In the next 24 hours, diabetes will claim the lives of over
   200 people, that’s 1400 friends, neighbors, coworkers or family
   members each week
   *        25.8 million Americans have diabetes, 7 million don’t know
   they have it

   For sponsorship information, to join the event planning committee, to
   donate auction items, for advance reservations- Contact Nancy
   Castrina at 804-225-8038, ext. 3287 or [27]ncastrina@diabetes.org.

   For updated information, check us out on Facebook: ADA Richmond!

   Buffet Table Decor Looking at Items Group

   Date: Saturday, June 2, 2012
   Time: 6:00 PM - 10:00 PM
   Address:
   200 North Boulevard
   Richmond, VA 23220

   We're sorry, the deadline for buying tickets for this event has passed.


